Lee KELLEY, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America et al., Appellees. No. 5552. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 4, 1930. Edgar Soule, of Houston, Tex., for appellant. Roy C. Sewell, of Houston, Tex. (Morris, Sewell, Taylor & Morris and W. J. Knight, all of Houston, Tex., on the brief), for appellees.

Before BRYAN and FOSTER, Circuit Judges, and GRUBB, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The decree in the above numbered and entitled cause is affirmed.
